Mobile Telecommunications Saudi Company (“Zain KSA”) Privacy Policy
Introduction
Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting your personal data. When you use this website or application, or make a purchase of a product or service, you automatically share personal information with us. To clarify, this Privacy Policy will explain what information we collect, what we do with it when you browse our sites or applications or purchase a product or service through them, how we use this information, with whom we may share it, for what reasons, and your choices regarding this use and necessary disclosures. From the e-store. We encourage you to read this Privacy Policy carefully as it contains important information alongside the terms of use for the site and electronic applications, so you are fully aware of how and why we use your personal data. This Privacy Policy complements any other privacy policies related to our site and is not intended to override any other privacy policies.
Information Collected and Methods of Collection
When you visit the site or application, we automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, operating system, IP address, time zone, and some cookies installed on your device. We also collect information about the pages and products you view while browsing the site, what sites or search terms led you to the site, and how you interact within the site. Additionally, we collect information you provide such as (name, mobile number, email address, and address).
We collect your information using the following techniques:
“Cookies” are data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique identifier. For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit
here
.
“Log files” track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring/exit pages, and date/time stamps.
“Web beacons,” “tags,” and “pixels” are electronic files used to record information about how you browse the Site.
In addition, when you make a purchase or attempt to, we collect specific personal information from you, including your name, billing address, shipping address, and payment information (including credit card number, payment card, email, and mobile number).
Legal Basis for Collecting and Processing Your Data:
Contractual:
Includes all activities we undertake to fulfill our contractual obligations to you.
Consent:
Such as for promotional and marketing messages.
Legitimate Interests:
Such as detecting fraud and improving our services.
Legal Obligation:
To comply with legal requirements from public authorities.
Purposes for Collecting Your Data:
Generally, we use the order information or personal information we collect for the following purposes:
To fulfill any order placed on the site (including processing payment information, shipping arrangements, and providing invoices and/or order confirmations).
To communicate with customers; review orders for potential risks or fraud; and when customers opt-in to share their preferences with us, to provide information or advertisements about our products or services.
To communicate with customers and address and resolve inquiries or complaints.
To assess potential risks and fraud, for example, using your IP address specifically, and to improve and develop our site generally (e.g., analyzing how customers browse and interact with the site, evaluating the success of our marketing and advertising campaigns).
To support operational processes and systems necessary for the continued provision of services with the required quality, and to provide accurate billing so the company can settle payments for products and services.
To send the latest product and service offers from Zain Saudi Arabia to customers.
To develop the content of the services and products offered to customers.
Sharing Your Personal Information
We will always maintain the confidentiality of the personal information you provide to us. Your personal information will not be shared with any third parties unless necessary to provide and deliver the product or service you requested. Your personal information will only be shared when required by Government Authorities in Saudi Arabia, or when it is necessary to share it with a third party to deliver the service and product, such as with shipping and delivery companies or for technical support. We will not transfer your data outside of the Kingdom except where adequate protection is in place and the transfer is lawful.
