Changes
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect, for example, changes to our practices or for operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The last update to this notice was on August 13, 2024.
User Rights
Right to be informed
: The legal basis for collecting their data and the purpose of collecting it.
Right of Access:
Customers can visit a branch to view their information in Zain's systems.
Right to Rectification:
If a customer wishes to correct their data, they can visit a branch for assistance in updating incorrect or outdated information.
Right to Withdraw Consent:
By contacting customer service to opt-out of promotional messages or through their Zain account.
Links to Other Sites
Our website or application may contain links to third-party websites, which are subject to different privacy policies.
Confidentiality and Disclosure of Information
Zain prioritizes the protection of personal data and is committed to taking reasonable technical and organizational precautions to prevent loss, misuse, or alteration of information. Zain will store collected information on secure servers and will only disclose this information as required by applicable laws and regulations in Saudi Arabia, or when Zain deems such disclosure necessary for providing services, products, technical support, or analytical purposes.
Zain commits not to sell, share, trade, lease, or disclose any information to any third party outside of Zain KSA or its subsidiaries without the customer’s consent. Third parties are required to maintain the confidentiality of the information and access it only as necessary to provide services and products.
